ful, and beautiful, An Orchid Astronomy wrestles with the grief we feel for the loss of those we love and grief for the changing world. In the language of mass extinction and the unknowable sky, Tasnuva Hayden fearlessly explores the nuances of personal collapse, sublimated desire, unfulfilled longing, and the ways we must move forward in the face of the impossible in poetry that dazzles like the moon on a midwinter night.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aClimatic changesvPoetry. 0aGriefvPoetry. 7aPOETRY / Women Authors.2bisacsh  aarctic circle.  aarctic.  acanadian author, calgary author, woman author, bipoc author.  acircumpolar.  aconcrete poetry.  aconstraint poetry.  aexperimental poetry.  alyricism.  anorway.  apolar.  aprose poetry.  asaami.  asurrealism.  avisual poetry.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311127214608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022z978311127419540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781773852720?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781773852720423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781773852720/original  a978-3-11-127214-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-127419-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles